-- Indian shares soar to record high; BoJ's surprise easing helps rally
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Fri Oct 31, 2014 05:56AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 31 (Reuters) - Indian shares surged nearly 2 percent on Friday to a record high for the second consecutive day after Bank of Japan's surprise expansion of its massive stimulus programme raised hopes for additional foreign inflows, boosting blue-chips such as Larsen & Toubro <LART.NS>.

The 30-share BSE index <.BSESN> rose as much as 2 percent to an all-time high of 27,894.32, while the NSE index <.NSEI> gained as much as 1.98 percent to mark a record high of 8,330.70, surpassing their previous highs hit on Thursday.Larsen & Toubro surged 3.6 percent, while Housing Development Finance Corp <HDFC.NS> rose 4.1 percent.